1
00:00:49,620 --> 00:00:53,820
=Camellias=

2
00:00:53,860 --> 00:00:56,780
=Episode 13=

3
00:01:34,959 --> 00:01:35,760
Feng Liu.

4
00:01:38,319 --> 00:01:38,959
My Lord!

5
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,480
What happened?

6
00:01:40,719 --> 00:01:41,920
He suddenly attacked me.

7
00:01:42,239 --> 00:01:42,920
How could that be?

8
00:01:44,359 --> 00:01:44,879
My Lord.

9
00:01:49,159 --> 00:01:50,519
Rong Zhaohua.

10
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,040
Holy Maiden,

11
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:52,799
please don't act rashly.

12
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:54,400
To the outside world,

13
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,319
you're already dead.

14
00:01:55,879 --> 00:01:56,840
If Rong Zhaohua

15
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,879
killed you now,

16
00:01:57,879 --> 00:01:58,840
no one would ever know.

17
00:01:59,200 --> 00:01:59,959
Besides,

18
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:02,079
My Lord risked everything to save you.

19
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:04,200
Don't let his efforts go to waste.

20
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:10,639
My Lord.

21
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:12,120
My Lord.

22
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,639
My Lord.

23
00:02:18,479 --> 00:02:19,159
You're awake.

24
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:19,919
My Lord,

25
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:20,960
you're finally awake.

26
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,199
The Holy Maiden

27
00:02:22,199 --> 00:02:23,719
has already bandaged your wounds.

28
00:02:24,039 --> 00:02:25,199
But what happened just now?

29
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,639
You actually attacked her?

30
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:30,719
My Lord.

31
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,360
My Lord.

32
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:33,560
You...

33
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:34,439
What's wrong with you, My Lord?

34
00:02:35,639 --> 00:02:36,159
My Lord.

35
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,039
My Lord.

36
00:02:37,319 --> 00:02:37,719
My Lord.

37
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:39,360
You hit me too, My Lord?

38
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,400
My Lord,

39
00:02:41,639 --> 00:02:42,240
are you alright?

40
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:43,479
My Lord!

41
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:45,719
My Lord.

42
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,039
My Lord.

43
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:19,159
My Lord.

44
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,280
Yukui.

45
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:47,639
My Lord.

46
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,000
Look at you.

47
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:50,759
You went full force on me,

48
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,479
but treated the Holy Maiden gently.

49
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:53,800
You'd rather hurt yourself

50
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,039
than hurt her,

51
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,759
choosing beauty over loyalty.

52
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:07,840
My Lord,

53
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,080
you haven't eaten all day.

54
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,000
Perhaps

55
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,400
you should have something.

56
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,800
Too sweet and cloying.

57
00:04:27,959 --> 00:04:28,800
Who likes this?

58
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,720
My Lord,

59
00:04:30,959 --> 00:04:31,879
you usually

60
00:04:31,879 --> 00:04:34,199
love these peach blossom cakes.

61
00:04:49,759 --> 00:04:50,639
This one's acceptable.

62
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:53,800
My Lord,

63
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,439
stay away from greasy food.

64
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,600
Holy Maiden.

65
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,560
From what I can see,

66
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,319
My Lord isn't poisoned.

67
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,120
He's been struck

68
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,560
by a secret art called Soul Swap.

69
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:10,879
Once this art takes hold,

70
00:05:10,879 --> 00:05:12,920
it changes you.

71
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,319
What you once liked,

72
00:05:14,319 --> 00:05:15,360
you'll dislike,

73
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,199
and what you disliked,

74
00:05:16,199 --> 00:05:17,680
you'll suddenly like.

75
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,519
From what I see,

76
00:05:21,519 --> 00:05:22,560
Holy Maiden,

77
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,839
My Lord

78
00:05:23,839 --> 00:05:25,600
went full force on me,

79
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,319
but toward you, he still seems to have

80
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,240
some shred of awareness.

81
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:33,319
So,

82
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:34,680
I'll leave My Lord

83
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,199
in your care.

84
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,120
You want some?

85
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,439
Get out!

86
00:06:09,519 --> 00:06:10,240
Zhaohua?

87
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:12,519
Zhaohua,

88
00:06:13,079 --> 00:06:14,000
I didn't know it was you.

89
00:06:14,759 --> 00:06:15,519
Are you hurt?

90
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,319
Your Majesty,

91
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:20,920
there's no need

92
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,600
to explain.

93
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:25,800
These wounds are nothing.

94
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:28,160
The wounds in your heart,

95
00:06:28,639 --> 00:06:29,800
those are what break my heart.

96
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,639
May I ask

97
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:35,879
what's troubling you?

98
00:06:38,399 --> 00:06:39,319
Just

99
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,759
some trivial matters of state.

100
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:46,079
Is that true?

101
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,160
I think

102
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:52,079
it's someone's disappearance

103
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,879
that's been troubling you.

104
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,000
I can't hide anything from you.

105
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,319
The reason I'm still thinking of her

106
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,680
is that

107
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,399
she has her uses.

108
00:07:08,279 --> 00:07:09,040
Zhaohua,

109
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,600
don't take it to heart.

110
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,360
I don't mind.

111
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:16,399
I know

112
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,519
that in Your Majesty's heart,

113
00:07:19,519 --> 00:07:21,639
I come first.

114
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:23,800
Other women,

115
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,600
they're just playthings.

116
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:30,439
If you want her back,

117
00:07:30,439 --> 00:07:31,839
I'll bring her to you.

118
00:07:31,839 --> 00:07:33,120
You'd really do that?

119
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,040
But rest assured,

120
00:07:37,399 --> 00:07:38,600
in my heart,

121
00:07:38,879 --> 00:07:40,319
you'll always be first.

122
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:46,680
I know.

123
00:07:54,639 --> 00:07:55,279
Let me go!

124
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:57,000
Let go!

125
00:07:58,199 --> 00:07:59,120
You witch,

126
00:07:59,959 --> 00:08:00,759
let me go!

127
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:02,800
Witch!

128
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,519
Call me that again,

129
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,519
and I'll have to punish you.

130
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:08,560
Do you think

131
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,519
I can't kill you?

132
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,720
Can't look at me?

133
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,040
Afraid you might remember something

134
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,720
and fall for me again?

135
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,120
What are you doing?

136
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:25,759
Hey.

137
00:09:08,559 --> 00:09:09,720
Don't think that just because
you treated my wounds,

138
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,799
I'll trust you.

139
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,200
(Don't think that just because)

140
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,480
(you took my injuries onto yourself,)

141
00:09:15,519 --> 00:09:16,799
(I'll go easy on you.)

142
00:09:16,799 --> 00:09:18,360
(If My Lord wakes up)

143
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,759
(and sees you here,)

144
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,279
(he'll be overjoyed.)

145
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:24,879
Come on.

146
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:26,240
Drink the medicine.

147
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,200
Not drinking?

148
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,799
Then don't blame me for being forceful.

149
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:40,440
Hey.

150
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,320
Holy Maiden.

151
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,399
How is My Lord?

152
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,679
He took the medicine?

153
00:10:29,679 --> 00:10:30,840
That's amazing, Holy Maiden!

154
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,720
Let me tell you.

155
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,440
All of us

156
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,240
tried one after another,

157
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,600
but none of us could get him
to drink it.

158
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:36,879
What did you do?

159
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,480
Never mind the method.

160
00:10:42,399 --> 00:10:43,960
They're just superficial wounds.

161
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:46,240
Now that he's taken the medicine,
he'll recover soon.

162
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,559
But the Soul Swap...

163
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:49,399
Right.

164
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,000
Holy Maiden,

165
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,399
do you know of any way

166
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:52,440
to break the Soul Swap?

167
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:54,039
Perhaps

168
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:56,600
we should find the answer within him.

169
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:59,279
Use his childhood memories

170
00:10:59,279 --> 00:11:01,000
to awaken who he is now.

171
00:11:02,639 --> 00:11:03,720
Do you know

172
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:05,720
what he loved as a child?

173
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,879
I don't know.

174
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:11,600
Wait.

175
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:12,879
I remember now.

176
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,000
Once,

177
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,159
when I was traveling with My Lord,

178
00:11:15,279 --> 00:11:16,320
he saw a mother

179
00:11:16,399 --> 00:11:18,240
flying a kite with her child,

180
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,000
and he looked so pleased.

181
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:20,679
Right?

182
00:11:20,919 --> 00:11:21,720
Yes, yes.

183
00:11:24,679 --> 00:11:25,960
If he had a choice,

184
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,200
My Lord

185
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,120
would probably just want

186
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,559
to be a free and unbound young master.

187
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,679
That's easy enough.

188
00:11:49,420 --> 00:11:52,740
♪The moon sinks in the west.
The cold lamp burns low♪

189
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:56,060
♪No one knocks upon
the mountain gate♪

190
00:11:56,380 --> 00:12:00,180
♪Snow-white winds and moonlight
touch me first♪

191
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:02,440
So?

192
00:12:02,879 --> 00:12:03,519
Do you like it?

193
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,399
You're the one playing, not me.

194
00:12:07,399 --> 00:12:08,279
Why would I like it?

195
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:14,140
♪Gathering red beans
for half a lifetime♪

196
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,399
Now you're playing.

197
00:12:15,399 --> 00:12:18,460
♪The Buddha speaks of countless paths♪

198
00:12:18,460 --> 00:12:22,020
♪How can one glance spanning ages
save a wandering soul♪

199
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:24,340
♪Trapped within
the space between your brows♪

200
00:12:24,399 --> 00:12:24,679
Hey.

201
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,559
I trust you.

202
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:35,340
♪The six senses cannot cleanse
the dust of the past♪

203
00:12:35,740 --> 00:12:39,060
♪In dreams, it's you.
Beyond dreams, no one♪

204
00:12:39,060 --> 00:12:42,380
♪Clinging to one obsession,
adrift in a sea of suffering♪

205
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:45,780
♪I can't forget
the stars in your eyes♪

206
00:12:45,780 --> 00:12:49,340
♪Our fate had already taken root♪

207
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:52,580
♪In this mortal world, there is only us♪

208
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:55,700
♪Hopelessly bound by love♪

209
00:13:31,279 --> 00:13:31,919
(I trust you.)

210
00:13:48,679 --> 00:13:49,480
Yukui.

211
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:18,380
♪The moon sinks in the west♪

212
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:20,300
♪The cold lamp burns low♪

213
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:23,620
♪No one knocks upon
the mountain gate♪

214
00:14:23,940 --> 00:14:27,740
♪Snow-white winds and moonlight
touch me first♪

215
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,420
♪Pear blossoms fill the courtyard♪

216
00:14:32,420 --> 00:14:33,940
♪Yet love and hate entwine♪

217
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:37,700
♪Bound by precepts,
yet craving worldly desires♪

218
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:41,700
♪Gathering red beans
for half a lifetime♪

219
00:14:42,860 --> 00:14:46,020
♪The Buddha speaks of countless paths♪

220
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:49,580
♪How can one glance spanning ages
save a wandering soul♪

221
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,900
♪Trapped within
the space between your brows♪

222
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:56,100
♪Falling deeper and deeper♪

223
00:14:56,540 --> 00:14:58,180
♪The green lamp sheds no light♪

224
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:59,700
♪Upon one who entered the path♪

225
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,900
♪The six senses cannot cleanse
the dust of the past♪

226
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:05,220
♪In dreams, it's you♪

227
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:06,620
♪Beyond dreams, no one♪

228
00:15:06,620 --> 00:15:09,940
♪Clinging to one obsession,
adrift in a sea of suffering♪

229
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:13,340
♪I can't forget the stars in your eyes♪

230
00:15:13,340 --> 00:15:16,900
♪Our fate had already taken root♪

231
00:15:16,900 --> 00:15:20,140
♪In this mortal world, there is only us♪

232
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:23,580
♪Hopelessly bound by love♪
